The nerve innervates the peroneus longus and brevis muscles, which evert the foot and stabilize the ankle. The sural nerve supplies sensation to the lateral foot and ankle, but it does not control any muscles. The deep peroneal nerve controls dorsiflexion of the foot and is not likely to be injured in this case. The saphenous nerve supplies sensation to the medial foot and ankle and does not control any muscles in the foot.
